                            <comment id="17083659" author="ksunitha" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2020 22:35:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can repro the issue using the Scala api on trunk.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-30065&quot; title=&quot;Unable to drop na with duplicate columns&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-30065&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-30065&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; explicitly removed the support for nested column resolution in drop. &#160; &#160;The change went into trunk and as well as the 2.4.5 branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.g in the test:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blame/master/sql/core/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/DataFrameNaFunctionsSuite.scala#L302&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blame/master/sql/core/src/test/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/DataFrameNaFunctionsSuite.scala#L302&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cloud_fan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cloud_fan&quot;&gt;cloud_fan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=imback82&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;imback82&quot;&gt;imback82&lt;/a&gt;&#160; &#160; This seems to be a regression. Is there a reason to remove this behavior?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17083666" author="imback82" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2020 22:47:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let me look into this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
